canonical:
  title: 金畵蘭贊 幷序
  author: 李穡
  language: lzh
  text: 金榮祿光秀近侍至正帝帝賜金畫蘭孟堅所作也榮祿告老携以東歸歸之公山壽翁侍中公公俾穡題其上蘭之馨號播于天庭寵錫近臣光耀東溟惟侍中公環衛帝宮感恩懷舊其心則同物得所歸妙矣天機臣題贊辭淚落沾衣
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 金畵蘭贊 幷序
  author: 李穡
  language: lzh
  text: 金榮祿光秀近侍至正帝。帝賜金畫蘭。孟堅所作也。榮祿告老。携以東歸。歸之公山壽翁侍中公。公俾穡題其上。蘭之馨號。播于天庭。寵錫近臣。光耀東溟。惟侍中公。環衛帝宮。感恩懷舊。其心則同。物得所歸。妙矣天機。臣題贊辭。淚落沾衣。
korean:
  title: 금화란 찬 병서
  author: 이색
  language: kor
  text: 김영록 광수(金榮祿光秀)가 지정황제(至正皇帝)를 가까이 모시고 있었는데, 황제는 금색으로 그린 난초를 주었다. 맹견(孟堅)이 그린 것이다. 영록(榮祿)이 벼슬에서 은퇴하고 그것을 가지고 우리나라에 와서 공산수옹시중공(公山壽翁侍中公)에게 주었다. 공이 색에게 그 위에 글을 써주기를 청하였다.난초의 향기로운 이름이 중국 조정에까지 전파되었다. 측근의 신하에게 사랑으로 주었던 것인데 우리나라에 빛이 비쳤도다. 오직 시중공(侍中公)은 황제의 궁전을 호위했었다. 은혜에 감격하며 옛 일을 회상할 제 그 마음이 같을 것이다. 물이 갈 곳을 얻었으니 묘하도다. 하늘의 기특함이여. 신 색(臣穡)이 찬사(贊辭)를 쓰니 눈물이 흘러 옷을 적시네.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0540_010_0250&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Eulogy on the Golden Orchid Painting with Preface
  author: Lee Saek
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Kim Young-rok, who served close to the Zhizheng Emperor, received from him an orchid painted in gold—a work of the master painter Meng Jian. When Young-rok retired from office, he brought it eastward and presented it to the Minister Gongshan Shou-weng. The Minister asked me to inscribe words upon it.

    The orchid's fragrant name spread even to the imperial court of the Middle Kingdom, a treasure bestowed upon a favored minister, now gracing our eastern realm with its splendor. The Minister alone once stood guardian at the Emperor's palace. Both he and I share the same heart—moved by imperial grace, dwelling in memories of former days. How wondrous that this treasure has found its rightful home, following the subtle workings of heaven's design. As I, your humble servant Saek, compose this eulogy, tears fall and dampen my robes.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Meng Jian (孟堅) was a celebrated Song dynasty painter known for his botanical works
  - key: ''
    value: The 'eastern realm' (東溟) refers to Korea, the poet's homeland
  - key: ''
    value: The title 侍中 (Attendant-in-Waiting) indicates a high court position close to the ruler
